page.title: 01LANDSCAPE
page.content: D-Square 04360273 extends from the former village of Toll Bar End, now a suburb of the city of Coventry, east to the village of Ryton on Dunsmore and beyond. The area is predominantly rural in character but the city of Coventry is having an increasingly urban influence on the area. Manufacturing and extractive industries as well as agriculture are found in the area. The river Avon meanders west then south through the area following a shallow valley with a NE-SW trend. Maximum height is 107m in the SE, minimum height is 50m along the river in the SW. The average height of the area is 70m. The roads and settlements are on the higher, dryer land; Ryton Bridge is situated at the narrowest point along the valley.
